---
/**
 * ai-evaluation/0001 · Figure 3 — "The eval harness" (dataset → runner → grader
 * → report, with the three grader types feeding the grader box and the
 * diff-vs-baseline gate). Copied VERBATIM from the source lesson (figure + svg +
 * figcaption incl. the footnote <sup>); an .astro component for the kebab-case
 * SVG reason.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 250"
        role="img"
        aria-label="An eval harness loads the golden dataset, runs the system per case, applies a grader, aggregates a score, and diffs it against the baseline to gate the merge."
    >
        <text x="320" y="18" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >The eval harness</text
        >

        <!-- pipeline -->
        <rect
            x="26"
            y="44"
            width="116"
            height="42"
            rx="8"
            fill="#eef0fb"
            stroke="#3d54c9"
            stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
        <text x="84" y="62" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" font-weight="700" fill="#3d54c9"
            >Golden dataset</text
        >
        <text x="84" y="76" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >(input, expected)</text
        >
        <rect
            x="170"
            y="44"
            width="116"
            height="42"
            rx="8"
            fill="#eef0fb"
            stroke="#3d54c9"
            stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
        <text x="228" y="62" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" font-weight="700" fill="#3d54c9"
            >Runner</text
        >
        <text x="228" y="76" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >execute per case</text
        >
        <rect
            x="314"
            y="44"
            width="116"
            height="42"
            rx="8"
            fill="#eef0fb"
            stroke="#3d54c9"
            stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
        <text x="372" y="62" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" font-weight="700" fill="#3d54c9"
            >Grader</text
        >
        <text x="372" y="76" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >score each output</text
        >
        <rect
            x="458"
            y="44"
            width="116"
            height="42"
            rx="8"
            fill="#eef0fb"
            stroke="#3d54c9"
            stroke-width="2"></rect>
        <text x="516" y="62" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" font-weight="700" fill="#3d54c9"
            >Report</text
        >
        <text x="516" y="76" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >aggregate score</text
        >
        <line x1="142" y1="65" x2="166" y2="65" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <line x1="286" y1="65" x2="310" y2="65" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <line x1="430" y1="65" x2="454" y2="65" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>

        <!-- three graders feeding the grader box -->
        <rect x="280" y="118" width="180" height="22" rx="5" fill="#e9f3ec" stroke="#2f5d3a"></rect>
        <text x="370" y="133" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" font-weight="700" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >programmatic / exact-match</text
        >
        <rect x="280" y="146" width="180" height="22" rx="5" fill="#fff7e6" stroke="#c2700f"></rect>
        <text x="370" y="161" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" font-weight="700" fill="#c2700f"
            >LLM-as-judge (calibrated)</text
        >
        <rect x="280" y="174" width="180" height="22" rx="5" fill="#eef0fb" stroke="#3d54c9"></rect>
        <text x="370" y="189" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" font-weight="700" fill="#3d54c9"
            >human (gold labels)</text
        >
        <line x1="372" y1="116" x2="372" y2="88" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>

        <!-- diff + gate -->
        <rect
            x="458"
            y="118"
            width="156"
            height="42"
            rx="8"
            fill="#ffffff"
            stroke="#111110"
            stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
        <text x="536" y="136" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >diff vs baseline</text
        >
        <text x="536" y="150" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f"
            >better? ship · worse? block</text
        >
        <line x1="516" y1="86" x2="516" y2="116" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>

        <rect x="40" y="210" width="560" height="30" rx="6" fill="#eef0fb" stroke="#3d54c9"></rect>
        <text x="320" y="229" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" font-weight="700" fill="#3d54c9"
            >Same inputs every run &rarr; reproducible &rarr; lives in CI &rarr; a drop below
            baseline blocks the merge.</text
        >
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        An eval harness is just a test framework for AI: a dataset, a runner that executes the
        system per case, a grader that scores each output, and a report you diff against the
        baseline. The golden set is your fixtures.<sup><a href="#s3" id="r3b">3</a></sup>
    </figcaption>
</figure>
